Define functions used¶

In [2]:
def haversine_distance(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2):
   r = 6371
   phi1 = np.radians(lat1)
   phi2 = np.radians(lat2)
   delta_phi = np.radians(lat2 - lat1)
   delta_lambda = np.radians(lon2 - lon1)
   a = np.sin(delta_phi / 2)**2 + np.cos(phi1) * np.cos(phi2) *   np.sin(delta_lambda / 2)**2
   res = r * (2 * np.arctan2(np.sqrt(a), np.sqrt(1 - a)))
   return np.round(res, 2)

Load data as prepared after Exploratory Data Analysis¶

In [3]:
data = pd.read_csv('../../data/raw/analyze_me.csv', index_col='delivery_id')
str_cols = ['customer_id', 'jumpman_id', 'vehicle_type', 'pickup_place']
datetime_cols = ['when_the_delivery_started', 'when_the_Jumpman_arrived_at_pickup', 'when_the_Jumpman_left_pickup', 'when_the_Jumpman_arrived_at_dropoff']

for col in str_cols:
    data[col] = data[col].astype("str")
    
for col in datetime_cols:
    data[col] = pd.to_datetime(data[col])

data['how_long_it_took_to_order'] = pd.to_timedelta(data['how_long_it_took_to_order'])  
    
data['deliv_time_timedelta'] = pd.to_timedelta(data['when_the_Jumpman_arrived_at_dropoff'] - data['when_the_delivery_started'])
data['deliv_time_minutes'] = data['deliv_time_timedelta'].astype('timedelta64[m]')    

distances = [haversine_distance(row.pickup_lat, row.pickup_lon, row.dropoff_lat, row.dropoff_lon) for row in data.itertuples()]
data['dist_in_km'] = distances

map_region = plt.imread('../../data/raw/map.png')
min_lat = 40.6490
max_lat = 40.8485
min_lon = -74.0180
max_lon = -73.9205
BBox = (min_lon, max_lon, min_lat, max_lat)

most_common_categories = data['item_category_name'].value_counts().nlargest(n=10, keep='all')

most_common_lats = data['pickup_lat'].value_counts().nlargest(n=20, keep='all').keys().tolist()
most_common_lons = data['pickup_lon'].value_counts().nlargest(n=20, keep='first').keys().tolist()

most_common_pickup_places = data['pickup_place'].value_counts().nlargest(n=20, keep='all').keys().tolist()
most_common_pickup_by_place_df = data[data['pickup_place'].isin(most_common_pickup_places)]
most_common_place_lats = most_common_pickup_by_place_df['pickup_lat'].tolist()
most_common_place_lons = most_common_pickup_by_place_df['pickup_lon'].tolist()
